v0.4.4
 - Cksfv (Check SFV) can create simple file verification (SFV) listings
   (program written by Bryan Call <bc fodder.org>) for having checksum on
   tar balls residing on the CD-ROM itself (23/01/2001)
 - Config.sh: LINKS - corrected the links for mkfs.* (were reversed -ai!)
 - added sshd support (etc/rc.d/rc.sshd, etc/rc.d/rc.sysinit and rd-base.sh)
 - moved all shell scripts into scripts/ directory and did the necessary
   modifications to all scripts and Makefile (22/01/2001)
 - added ReiserFS support to rd-base.sh/Config.sh of Falk Stern (21/01/2001)
 - start-restore.sh/clone-dsk.sh: bug fixes from Marco Milita (21/01/2001)
 - rd-base.sh: added TAPE_DEV to etc/recovery (bug report from Marco 21/01)
 - usr/bin/man: changed $1 to $1.gz (21/01/2001)
 - rd-base.sh: keep a previous version of mkcdrec.log (21/01/2001)
 - rd-base.sh: fixed the assumption that disk names are always 3 characters	
   long (eg. hda), but could be shorter (md) or longer (sdaa) (19/01/2001)
